
<b>Click in tiles (requires Java ).</b>
(name : <tt class="wims_code_words">clicktile</tt>)
<br/>

An applet shows colored tiles. Some polygonal lines or (exclusive) one point
can be showed. Some tiles must be colored differently by the student by clicking on them.

<p>Command <tt class="wims_code_words">\embed</tt> must be used. Each tile is given by the left-top corner
by something like <tt class="wims_code_words">integer:integer</tt>. 
The first line of the command <tt class="wims_code_words">\embed</tt> is the size X x Y  in pixels of the applet.
The second line inside  <tt class="wims_code_words">[</tt> <tt class="wims_code_words">]</tt> contains commands precising the colored tiles
which will be presented (they can not be modified by the student) : for example,
<pre>
\embed{r1, 200 x 200
[xrange -5,5
yrange -5,5
background_color yellow
square blue,1:1,1:2,1:3
square green,2:3,2:4
point red,0:0]}
</pre>
The bounds (<tt class="wims_code_words">xrange</tt> and <tt class="wims_code_words">yrange</tt>) must be integers. 
The good answer is given by lines as
<tt class="wims_code_words">color,a:b,c:d</tt>
The tile points must be of the form <tt class="wims_code_words">a:b</tt>
wherein <tt class="wims_code_words">a</tt> and <tt class="wims_code_words">b</tt> are integers.

For the background draw, one of the following lines is possible
<pre>
polygon white,0:0,0:1,1:1
point red,0:0
line white,-5:0,5:0
</pre><br/>
It is also possible to present an image in the background. 
<pre>copy,x,y,url</pre>
If done with flydraw, the url is the result of the function <tt class="wims_code_words">draw()</tt>. It is recommended
to take the same <tt class="wims_code_words">xrange</tt> and <tt class="wims_code_words">yrange</tt>. 

The variable <tt class="wims_code_words">reply</tt>n is the matrix of selected tiles (one line for each color).
If the line
<pre>
return_all_objects yes
</pre>
is in the second line of the command <tt class="wims_code_words">\embed</tt>, all tiles will be returned in <tt class="wims_code_words">reply</tt>n.
The variable <tt class="wims_code_words">sc_reply</tt>n is equal to 0.5 if all clicked tiles are correct, but not of the asked color

<p>An empty variable can be put in the good reply. The analysis must be done with conditions in this
case.
</p>
<p>
<b>Example</b> : 
<pre>
\statement{
  \embed{r1,200 x 200
  [xrange -5,5
   yrange -5,5
   background_color yellow
   square blue,1:1,1:2,1:3
   square green,2:3,2:4
   line white,-5:0,5:0
  ]}
}
\answer{}{blue,1:0,1:-1,1:-2; green,2:-2,2:-3}{type=clicktile}
</pre>
